    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "According to the Comprehensive Peace Agreement (CPA) the disqualified Maoist combatants shall be discharged and rehabilitated into society. These 4008 individuals were disqualified through the UNMIN led verification process because they were either under the age of 18 at the date of the peace accord or they were recruited to the Maoist army after this date. The primary objective of this project is to have as many of the VMLRs as possible involved in gainful employment or livelihood opportunities. To achieve this, the project is framed around two complimentary outcomes: 1) VMLRs were supported in their socio-economic rehabilitation; and2) Communities were engaged in supporting the rehabilitation of VMLR participants."
      },
      "ne": null
